   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (Moving in ``i'' category.) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-U.S.-TENSIONS (Moscow) _ In a fresh sign of the tensions
that have grown between the United States and Russia since the war
in Kosovo, Moscow has ordered an American military attache to leave
the country, American officials said Saturday. By Michael R.
Gordon.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-BRITAIN (Pristina, Kosovo) _ British peacekeeping troops
shot two Kosovar Albanians dead Saturday night, one of them a
well-known Kosovo Liberation Army soldier. Two civilians were
severely wounded in the same incident, which occurred during a wild
street celebration marking the Kosovo Albanians' freedom from
Serbian rule. By John Kifner.
</P>
