   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Sunday, July 4 and thereafter. For questions about stories, contact
Stew Slavin at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   LA-NET-LOBBY (Los Angeles) _ Reflecting a battle over whether
cable TV companies will win the right to use cable for high-speed
Internet access, the companies involved have outspent all other
lobbyists so far this year, city records show. By Deborah Sullivan.
(Will move in the ``n'' California news file.)
</P>
