   COP-POET (Los Angeles) _ By night, Los Angeles police Officer
Sunil Dutta reads crooks their rights on some of the meanest
streets in America. By day, the 35-year-old with a doctorate in
biology reads the verse of renowned Indian poet Ghalib and
painstakingly translates it into English. By Troy Anderson. (Will
move in the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news file.)
