<P>
   BUSH-MONEY _ How the heck do you raise $36.25 million in four
months? We explain the Bush money machine and pose the question:
Will his record-busting total change the face of presidential
campaigning. (Herman, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   PRESIDENTS-BUSH _ AUSTIN _ Texas Gov. George W. Bush has had
astounding success in raising money for his presidential campaign,
collecting more than $20 million in about four months. In amassing
that sum, Bush has tapped many of the donors who gave to his
father's campaigns. But in yet another sign of the son's
extraordinary fund-raising prowess, many of those who gave to
George the Elder are giving even more to George the Younger.
(Greenberger, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-MARKETS _ SOUTH PHOENIX, Ariz. _ Returning to a domestic
focus as the political season heats up, President Clinton embarks
Monday on a four-day transcontinental caravan to highlight the need
to invest in what he calls America's ``new markets.'' Clinton will
visit Appalachia, the Mississippi Delta, two inner cities, an
Indian reservation and a Hispanic community to sell Congress and
corporate America on the idea. The trip also has political
overtones; traditional Democratic constituencies appear to be
another target of his message. (Shepard, Cox News Service). WITH
PHOTOS.
</P>
