   KOSOVO-CIVIL _ PRISTINA, Yugoslavia _ There's no real police
force here yet, so your children can drive if you give them the
keys. No one is sure who owns what, so you can stake your claim to
the tractor next door or the mammoth metal plant in the
countryside. There are no courts, congress or tax collectors and
the man in charge works in a badly-trashed building where the doors
don't lock and employees are urged to take their computers home
with them. Welcome to U.N. Country, also known as Kosovo. (Kaplow,
Cox News Service). WITH PHOTOS.
