<P>
   COXNET FOCUS 0703 CONGRESS SPENDING _ As fireworks etch the
skies with bright colors for the last Independence Day of this
century, the majestic dome of the U.S. Capitol will look much as it
did 99 years ago. But almost everything else about Capitol Hill has
changed in a century that brought an explosion of staff,
construction and bureaucracy _ not to mention lobbyists _ to
Congress. (Malone, Cox Washington Bureau). Art includes 4-column
graphic illustrating rise in the cost of Congress, 2-column color
photo of fountain to be refurbished, 18-pica color photo of Strom
Thurmond, 18-pica color photo of Congress in session, and two color
mugshots of lawmakers Dennis Hastert and Dick Gephardt.
