<HEADER>
A8489 &Cx1f; taf-z
u a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-NY-DOUBLE-MURDER-NYT &LR;      07-03 0479
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NY-DOUBLE-MURDER-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MAN ADMITS KILLING TWO GIRLFRIENDS, POLICE SAY 
</HEADLINE>
  (lb) 
 By KIT R. ROANE   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ A Brooklyn man who phoned the police on Friday to say
that he had killed his girlfriend and his ex-girlfriend has been
charged with one of the murders and will be charged with the other,
law-enforcement officials said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Detectives arrested the man, Lionel Michael King, 41, around
10:30 a.m. Friday at his home shortly after he called a 911
operator to report the crimes, the police said.
</P>
<P>
   They added that he has been charged with second-degree murder
and criminal possession of a weapon in the stabbing death of Patsy
Niles, the mother of his 5-year-old daughter, in her home in
Brooklyn.
</P>
<P>
   Mary DeBourbon, a spokeswoman for the Queens district attorney's
office, said that King would face similar charges in the killing of
Dionne DeSouza, 29, who was found stabbed to death at her home in
Queens. Ms. DeBourbon said King would most likely be arraigned
there on Monday or Tuesday after arraignments were completed in the
Brooklyn case.
</P>
<P>
   According to law-enforcement officials, King went to Ms.
DeSouza's home around 6 a.m. on Friday and began to argue with her
about their relationship. At some point he became violent, grabbing
a knife and stabbing her repeatedly in the neck and chest before
running out to his car and driving off, they said.
</P>
<P>
   King then drove to Brooklyn to the home of his former
girlfriend, Ms. Niles, 29. He confronted her around 7 a.m. near the
front door of the building where she lived, stabbed her repeatedly
and fled, officials said.
</P>
<P>
   Ms. Niles' sister-in-law, who spoke on the condition of
anonymity, said that she and Ms. Niles' three children were
awakened by banging on the front door of the family's second-story
apartment. When the door was opened, the woman said, Ms. Niles fell
to the ground, saying: ``Mikey stabbed me. Please don't let me
die.'' She died of her wounds moments later, the police said.
</P>
<P>
   Bloody and confused, King then went to the apartment of another
woman he knew in Brooklyn and demanded to be let inside, the
officials said. When she refused his request, King started
confessing to the murders while sitting outside her door, they
said.
</P>
<P>
   As the woman was phoning a 911 operator to report the incident,
King took off again, this time returning to his apartment and
calling 911 himself. According to the police, he told the operator
about the murders and indicated that he wanted to kill himself.
</P>
<P>
   The police found him inside his apartment, bleeding from several
wounds on his hands and arms. He was treated at Kings County
Hospital, where the police took him into custody.
</P>
<P>
   King had been charged 18 months ago with assaulting Ms. Niles,
but the charges were dropped when she refused to testify, the
police said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
