<HEADLINE>
HOSPITAL ATTACKER KILLS FATHER, POLICE SAY 
</HEADLINE>
  (lb) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ A 49-year-old Brooklyn man casually walked into a Bay
Ridge hospital room on Saturday, killed his ailing father by
slashing his throat, and then struck both his sister and another
patient in the head with a hammer, the police said.
</P>
<P>
   The police said the attack occurred after the man, Joseph
Ranieri Jr. arrived at Victory Memorial Hospital to visit his
74-year-old father around noon.
</P>
<P>
   After killing his father, Joseph Ranieri Sr., Ranieri struck his
sister, Linda, 49, who was already visiting, and his father's
88-year-old roommate, Michael Dambrose, said Officer Chris
Cottingham, a police spokesman. Dambrose was taken to Lutheran
Medical Center in Brooklyn with serious head injuries, the police
said.
</P>
<P>
   Cottingham said that hospital security officers stopped the
younger Ranieri as he was leaving the room. The police arrived
moments later and took Ranieri into custody. Cottingham said
Ranieri had not been charged, and investigators were questioning
him at the 68th Precinct station house.
</P>
<P>
   The police said that Ms. Ranieri was still at Victory Memorial
in serious condition, suffering from head trauma.
</P>
<P>
   A woman who answered the telephone at the hospital on Saturday
said, ``There is no comment, and there is no one available at the
moment.''
</P>
</TEXT>
