``Welfare used to come easier,'' says Ms. Rhoden, who finds keeping
herself going has been hard. With the welfare rolls in Wisconsin
down 90 percent, many of those left behind are accustomed to
difficult lives. ``I'm not going to lie -- I used to play the
system to be with my kids,'' she says. (Nicole Bengiveno/New York
