<HEADLINE>
SCORNED ON FOURTH OF JULY
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By E.J. MONTINI  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   In keeping with Independence Day tra dition, the U.S.
Departments of Justice and Veterans Affairs have decided to hold an
old-fashioned barbecue.
</P>
<P>
   They've dug a narrow pit in central Phoenix, stoked it with hot
coals and built over it a sturdy spit, on which they hope to slowly
roast a 77-year-old war hero named Bob Deheer.
</P>
<P>
   ``I can't believe they're going forward with this,'' said
Deheer's attorney, Mi chael Rooney. ``I can't believe our gov
ernment would waste its money going after an elderly veteran. And
for what?''
</P>
<P>
   For 75 bucks.
</P>
<P>
   In May, Deheer got into a scuffle with officers at the Carl T.
Hayden Veterans Affairs Medical Center. The vet was in town to get
his hearing aids adjusted.
</P>
<P>
   He has trouble walking long distances now and couldn't find an
open handi capped parking space in the crowded lot.
</P>
<P>
   So, he tried to park in one of the spaces near the front door
marked ``VIP,'' areas supposedly for federal inspectors in town
that day.
</P>
<P>
   Deheer needed to use the restroom and figured a guy like him,
who'd earned a Bronze Star and a Purple Heart as a ma chine-gunner
in France, was as much a VIP as any two-bit bureaucrat.
</P>
<P>
   He was wrong.
</P>
<P>
   At least in the eyes of the federal cops on parking lot duty. &QL; 
VERBAL FISTICUFFS
</P>
<P>
   They got into a war of words with De heer and wound up hauling
him off in handcuffs, locking him in a cell, then is suing him two
citations _ a $50 disor derly conduct charge and a $25 ticket for
failing to comply with a federal officer.
</P>
<P>
   The feds say that Deheer was abusive, even physically
threatening, and that he refused to use parking spaces that
officers pointed out to him. Deheer denies this. He says the delay
in getting to a restroom actually caused him to urinate on himself.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not about to pay those fines,'' he told me last month,
when I first wrote about this. ``It just isn't right. I don't care
if they put me in jail.''
</P>
<P>
   They won't.
</P>
<P>
   But they do plan to take him to court. Rather than drop the
charges and apolo gize to Deheer, which would be the right thing,
the VA, in partnership with the U.S. attorney, decided last week to
take the case before a federal magistrate. A trial is set for late
August.
</P>
<P>
   Maybe they need to improve their con viction percentages, which
dropped re cently when an appeals court overturned guilty verdicts
against Fife Symington _ an embarrassing setback for prosecutors
who'd spent years chasing the former governor. Now, the government
will use its full powers to take down Bob Deheer.
</P>
<P>
   Over a parking lot beef.
</P>
<P>
   ``Is this what we asked GIs like Mr. Deheer to risk their lives
for?'' attorney Rooney asked. &QL; 
ANSWER IN DOUBLE TALK
</P>
<P>
   I put the same question to the folks at the VA and the U.S.
Attorney's Office. What I got in return was double talk.
</P>
<P>
   `'We are not policymakers,'' a spokes woman from the U.S.
Attorney's Office said. ``Our job is to take cases referred to
us.''
</P>
<P>
   Apparently, without regard for common sense or common decency.
</P>
<P>
   If the U.S. government beats Bob De heer, it'll be because it
has all the money and all the power. Which is because De heer and
millions like him once stood against guns and bombs and cannon
shells and did not yield.
</P>
<P>
   Maybe that's why the old vet won't yield, now, when the
government he risked his life to defend has its big guns pointed at
him.
</P>
<P>
   The words in the Declaration of Inde pendence, celebrated today,
still apply.
</P>
<P>
   Some truths really are self-evident.
</P>
<P>
   Although, at the VA and the Justice Department, they don't seem
to believe all men are created equal.
</P>
<P>
   Or that those who so served their coun try have been endowed
with certain un alienable rights.
</P>
<P>
   Which makes it easy to see how bu reaucrats with no lives and no
respect for liberty would believe so fervently in the pursuit of
Bob Deheer. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
